1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,700
AgentPay Firewall turns autonomous payments into policy-controlled infrastructure.

2
00:00:05,700 --> 00:00:12,500
AI agents can call paid APIs, but they should not spend from a wallet without rules.

3
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:20,700
The user defines the mandate: max request cost, daily budget, approved services, network, asset, risk score, and human approval.

4
00:00:20,700 --> 00:00:27,300
First, the agent calls a paid wallet-risk API. The server returns an HTTP 402 payment-required challenge.

5
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:35,300
The firewall checks every gate. Because the request is safe, it signs, retries, and receives a settlement receipt.

6
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:43,800
Now the unsafe path: a larger request from an untrusted service gets the same challenge, but policy fails before signing.

7
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:48,500
No signature leaves the wallet. No payment is authorized. The audit log records the exact reason.

8
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:53,400
Most demos prove that agents can pay. AgentPay Firewall proves they can pay within user-controlled policy.
